@David Connell
In Aberdeenshire, Scotland, the local dialect (Doric) adds -ie to words to make a diminutive, used with children. So bookie, coatie, cupie , and so on. 
Possibly many languages have ways of doing this.

@Fred The clue says 'grain milled into flour.' It doesn't say anything about a 'type' of grain. 

Example: 'Water frozen into cubes' = 'ice'. Agreed? State of water, not type of water. Same thing.

And following the theme, a finger sandwich solve for a mini version (let) of a submarine sandwich (sub) is a fine clue.

@MJFROMBUFFALO

There’s an xkcd.com cartoon where a company’s website gives you a choice:

Either “I accept the app” or “No but ask me every time!”

@Calhouri 

I read your comment at the exact moment "Good fun" was sung by Pharrell in the Daft Punk song Get Lucky, after I had just turned on the radio. Lovely random synchronicity! 

VENDING MACHINE was the first theme I filled in, but it took a bit to get it. To me, "mart" conjures a certain type of emporium; thinking of a vending machine as a mini microcosm of that really tickles my imagination somehow!

@sotto voce 

I’ve watched many Rockin1000 videos (but not that one), even have tshirt (a gift from my son), but I never knew their origin story.

Thanks, Sotto!

@Tom Wild 

I hope your tears are not because my post might have inadvertently sounded like my dad has passed. I'm sorry if that's the case! 
He's 91 now. It's just that I gather memories  as I go. ;-)

@Warren

That's a tough memory. 
Isn't it strange how music can unearth a tough memory but still be beautiful to our ears? It almost makes no sense. I'm certainly glad you get to still love the song.

@sotto voce 

It’s odd how fundamental music can be, even though I’m not much of a musician. We listened to his labored breaths all night, in/out, in/out, in/out, in/out. 4/4 time. In the wee hours, in/out…then nothing. I thought of David Bromberg’s  comment that some of the best notes he’s ever played were rests. Just breathe? Maybe this was for the best? The hospital staff didn’t rush around, nobody came in to scrupulously record the time of death. They had already written him off, probably days ago. Such a good life and such a good song.

